# Gherkin Formatting Rules

## Given, When, Then

- **Given** – Preconditions and state
- **When** – The action under test (use page objects; verify world data before calling)
- **Then** – Verification and assertions (immediate UI checks)

**And** – Use when chaining steps of the same type. Use `And` for the second and subsequent steps instead of repeating Given/When/Then.

**Step definitions** – Declare each step once. Use Given for setup, When for actions, Then for verification—matching the keyword used in the feature.

## Cucumber Data Tables

**Vertically align all `|` pipe characters** in Examples and Data Tables so columns line up.

✅ **GOOD** - Aligned columns:
```gherkin
  Examples:
    | Field            | Error Message |
    | First Name       | "Required"    |
    | Last Name        | "Required"    |
    | Employee Name    | "Required"    |
    | Username         | "Required"    |
```

❌ **BAD** - Misaligned:
```gherkin
  Examples:
    | Field | Error Message |
    | First Name | "Required" |
    | Last Name | "Required" |
```

Pad cell content with spaces so that each column's right edge (before the next `|`) aligns across all rows.

## Tags on New Features

When adding a new feature file, add `@regression` at the Feature level so its scenarios are included in regression runs.

```gherkin
@regression
@your-area
Feature: Your Feature Name
```
